Findings: A left central venous catheter is seen terminating in the lower SVC. Again seen is elevation of the right hemidiaphragm and small pleural effusion and atelectasis at the base of the right lung. The cardiomediastinal silhouette and hilar contours are grossly unchanged. There is no evidence of pneumothorax. Thoracolumbar fusion hardware is seen unchanged in appearance.
Impression: Small pleural effusion and atelectasis at the base of the right lung.
